# ==================== IBPS PLATFORM - ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES ====================

# ==================== LOCAL DEVELOPMENT ====================
# For running locally, use MongoDB running on your machine:
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/ibps-platform
PORT=5000

# ==================== MONGODB ATLAS (Cloud) ====================
# For production/cloud deployment, use MongoDB Atlas:
# MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster0.xxxxx.mongodb.net/ibps-platform?retryWrites=true&w=majority
# PORT=5000

# ==================== QUICK SETUP INSTRUCTIONS ====================
# 
# 1. CREATE .env FILE
#    Copy this file and rename to: .env (in the server/ folder)
#    Do NOT commit .env to Git (it's in .gitignore)
#
# 2. FOR LOCAL MONGODB
#    Install MongoDB Community Edition from: https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/community
#    Run MongoDB: mongod (on Windows, Linux, or Mac)
#    Connection String: mongodb://localhost:27017/ibps-platform
#
# 3. FOR MONGODB ATLAS (CLOUD)
#    - Create account: https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas
#    - Create free cluster
#    - Create database user (username & password)
#    - Get connection string from Atlas
#    - Replace in MONGODB_URI below
#    - Format: mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/database-name
#    - Make sure to:
#      * Replace "username" with your database user
#      * Replace "password" with your database password
#      * Allow 0.0.0.0/0 in Network Access (for development)
#
# 4. AFTER SETUP
#    Run: npm install
#    Run: npm start
#    Server will be available at: http://localhost:5000
#
# ==================== VARIABLES EXPLAINED ====================
#
# MONGODB_URI
#   - Connection string to your MongoDB database
#   - Local: mongodb://localhost:27017/database-name
#   - Cloud: mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/database-name
#
# PORT
#   - Port number where server runs
#   - Default: 5000
#   - In production, set to: 3000 or higher
#   - Make sure port is not already in use
#
# ==================== TROUBLESHOOTING ====================
#
# Error: "connect ECONNREFUSED 127.0.0.1:27017"
#   → MongoDB is not running locally
#   → Either: 1) Start MongoDB or 2) Use MongoDB Atlas
#
# Error: "MongoServerSelectionError"
#   → Check MongoDB URI is correct
#   → Check username/password for Atlas
#   → Check network access in Atlas
#
# Error: "Port 5000 already in use"
#   → Change PORT to 5001 or higher
#   → Or kill process using port 5000
#
# ==================== END OF .env.example ====================
